A '''butter curler''' is a [[kitchen tool]] designed to produce decorative [[butter]] shapes for use in food decoration. It can also be used to make [[chocolate]] and [[wax]] shavings. In typical use, the material to be cut is chilled slightly while the curler is dipped into hot water to ease the cutting.<ref>{{cite book | last=Berolzheimer | first=Ruth | year=1988 | title=Culinary Arts Institute Encyclopedic Cookbook | edition=1st | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=eoktyOUwM1oC&lpg=PA45&dq=%22butter%20curler%22&pg=PA45#v=onepage&q=%22butter%20curler%22&f=false | accessdate=2010-12-24 }} page 45.</ref>

