'''FS Me''' is a [[typeface]]/[[font]] that has been described as the first to have been designed in consultation with a group of people with [[learning disabilities]]<ref name=mencap>[https://www.mencap.org.uk/node/7177 Mencap font is world class], Mencap, 9 May 2009</ref> and designed for use by this population.<ref name="creativereview.co.uk"/><ref name="creativereview">{{cite web|url=http://www.creativereview.co.uk/cr-blog/2008/may/the-new-face-of-mencap|title=Creative Review - The New Face of Mencap|publisher=creativereview.co.uk|accessdate=26 September 2014}}</ref> It was developed by Jason Smith in response to a commission from the charity [[Mencap]] in 2008. It was the only font featured in the D&AD Annual 2009 covering advertising and design work.
