'''Industrial finishing''' is any kind of secondary process done to any metal, plastic, or wood product used in a common market such as automotive, [[Original Equipment Manufacturer|OEM]], telecommunications or point-of-purchase. The most common commodity in the industrial finishing market is plastic parts. These can be injection molded, thermoformed, extruded or vacuum formed. Most parts are painted but can be [[Pad printing|pad printed]] or [[silkscreening|silkscreened]].

One finishing process is [[vacuum metalising]].

